node.text:
Bone carving is an ancient art form popularized by royals in India around the 16th century. More recently, a shrinking market and scarcity of materials have pushed many carvers away from the craft. Jalaluddin Akhtar and his son Akheel are determined to keep the craft alive in Lucknow.

#BoneCarving #India #Handmade #FamilyRun #Lucknow #IndianCraft

node.title: How bone carvers in India are keeping a prehistoric art alive

node.text:
YouTube is filled with viral videos of Jeeps scaling vertical rock walls. While most of these vehicles are modified, there's a reason Jeeps are so often the choice of these extreme off-roaders, or rock crawlers. From their unmatched standard features to the number of ways they can be modified, Jeeps are the perfect tool for crawling.

node.text:
Starting a weed business isn't easy. It can take $1 million in startup capital to even get a license. And to keep a cannabis business going? That means jumping through complicated regulation hoops. If they can play the game right, cannabis entrepreneurs could be set up for success in an exploding marijuana industry. But with weed still federally illegal, companies could face fines or jail time if they don't follow the rules. We visited three companies in Colorado and Oregon to see how they're dealing with the ever-changing regulations. Could things get easier if weed becomes federally legal?

Featuring @magichourcannabis.

#Marijuana #THC #Cannabis #Business #WeedBusiness

node.title: Why starting a marijuana business is so hard | Big Business

node.text:
One of the biggest cargo planes in the world, the C-17 Globemaster III has a payload capacity of 172,000 pounds. The massive plane is used in a variety of missions, including evacuation efforts and troop transport in Afghanistan after the Taliban took control of Kabul in August 2021. This aircraft requires only three crew members to fly: a pilot, a copilot, and a loadmaster. Insider spent three days at Travis Air Force Base, where we observed the training required to fly these giant $340 million feats of engineering. That training included mastering the flight simulator, planning the proper execution of a mission, and then putting that mission into action with an instructor pilot and performing it in the sky.

node.title: What it takes to fly the $340 million C-17 Globemaster III | Boot Camp

node.text: Sam Bernstein and April Koh press pause on their busy days as entrepreneurs to reflect on the companies they each founded at a young age. For Bernstein, that was Table22, which helps restaurants create new revenue streams through subscription kits. For Koh, that was Spring Health, which connects employers to mental wellness resources for workers. Their conversation over coffee, thanks to Philips Espresso 3200 LatteGo, reveals a new style of leadership that prioritizes openness and vulnerability and underscores the need to step away and recharge.

node.title: Two young entrepreneurs reflect on the strength that comes from self-care

Durian’s smell is famously divisive. But in Asia and the Pacific Islands, durian is known as the “King of Fruit.” Nonthaburi, Thailand, is known for cultivating some of the most sought-after durian varieties: Kan Yao and Mon Thong. In 2019, one Nonthaburi, or Nont, durian sold at auction for $48,000. So, what makes this pungent, spiky fruit so expensive?

From finishing each piece with a glossy shine to cutting down blocks of wood by hand — it takes over 200 artisans to craft just one Steinway grand piano. Steinway is one of the most famous piano brands in the world, and depending on the model, it can be one of the priciest. A Steinway Model D ebony concert piano will cost you $187,000. Famous pianists and music icons like Billy Joel and Lang Lang play on Steinway pianos. But with several other high-end piano brands on the market, why are musicians so drawn to Steinway? And why are these pianos so expensive?

node.text:
Pottery is a traditional industry in Gaza, supported by families like Sabri Atallah's. But decades of armed conflict and political strife have put these artisans' livelihoods at risk. We visited Sabri Atallah & Sons Pottery Factory before, during, and after the May 2021 attacks to see how he is keeping the craft alive.

Sabri only sells his pottery locally and does not have a website.

#Gaza #Israel #Palestine #Pottery #PotteryShop #MakingPottery #Familyrun #PotteryFactory

node.title: How This Pottery Shop Survived Six Decades Of War And Conflict In Gaza

node.text:
Hogoè Kpessou is a designer best known for @hogoekpessou, her eponymous brand of backpacks emblazoned with bees. Kpessou used $10,000 from her mom to start the business and expects to hit seven figures in revenue by the beginning of next year.

She talked with us about her career beginnings and her entrepreneurial journey. Click the link in our bio to read the full story.

Story by @dominicmadori.

(Credit: Hogoè Kpessou)
#luxuryhandbags #HogoèKpessou #smallbusiness

Photo of a model and a handbag on the beach with the text, "Black entrepreneurs continue to stand out in the luxury industry, which is estimated to be worth 297 billion by 2026, according to research firm Global Industry Analysts. Continuing that trend is Hogoè Kpessou, founder of the eponymous brand that sells handbags and accessories."
Photo of a model on the phone holing a handbag with the text, "Kpessou used $10,000 from her mom to start the business and expects to hit seven figures in revenue by the beginning of next year."

When she launched her brand last October, she named it after herself to wash away the negative association she harbored toward her name."
Photo of a Hogoè Kpessou with the quote, "I have people asking me how to say my name properly and asking how to spell it," she told Insider. "That was a good choice on my part."

node.text:
According to the Bureau of Labor Statistics, the number of jobs added in August came in dismally below economists’ expectations, showing yet another bump in the road for America’s economic recovery.

August’s data also shows that the pandemic’s newest surge — and not enhanced unemployment benefits — is responsible for workers staying home.

Click the link in our bio to read the full story.

Bone carving is an ancient art form popularized by royals in India around the 16th century. More recently, a shrinking market and scarcity of materials have pushed many carvers away from the craft. Jalaluddin Akhtar and his son Akheel are determined to keep the craft alive in Lucknow.

Traffic jams in Europe, Southeast Asia, and China are posing a new challenge to the supply chain, indicating that Americans may need to get used to waiting around and paying more for the things they want.

These global traffic jams are sending prices up for many goods, with fewer discounts — just as the holidays roll around.

Click the link in our bio to read the full story.

(Credit: Getty Images)

node.text:
US businesses created roughly a third of the jobs expected in August as COVID cases rebounded and governments reinstated some economic restrictions.

About 8.4 million Americans remained unemployed when the government's survey period ended in mid-August. Similarly, the unemployment rate fell to 5.2% from 5.4%. That matched the estimate for a rate of 5.2%.

The average hourly wage rose 17 cents, or 0.6%, to $30.73. Economists expected the average to rise 0.3% through the month.

To read more from the August jobs report, click the link in our bio.

Story by Ben Winck.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business Insider on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'INSIDER Bumble creates relief fund for women in Texas to seek abortions after the Supreme Court refused to block a controversial 'heartbeat bill''.

node.text:
Bumble has created a relief fund for women and people across the gender spectrum seeking abortions. The company vowed to "keep fighting against regressive laws."

The women-centered dating app announced in a tweet Wednesday that "Starting today, Bumble has created a relief fund supporting the reproductive rights of women and people across the gender spectrum who seek abortions in Texas."

The move comes after the Supreme Court did not block a Texas law limiting abortion to the first six weeks of pregnancy. 

For more information, click the link in our bio. 

Story by Anna Cooban.

[Credit: Vivien Killilea/Getty Images for Bumble]

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business Insider on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Premium INSIDER Pay raises are making Wall Street junior bankers richer. But muddled rollouts have left some feeling short-changed amid a fierce battle for talent.'.

node.text:
Offer letters from Evercore that went out in late August contained exciting news: first-year associates joining the investment bank in summer 2022 would earn a base salary of $185,000, making them the highest-paid on Wall Street. 

Current associates, who make $160,000 per year, told Insider that Evercore hasn't yet announced when and if they'll be getting a bump, too.

The silence has irked some existing staffers, one of whom called it "definitely a little disrespectful." The Evercore associate, who spoke on the condition of anonymity, expects the company to raise existing associates' salaries accordingly, but still thinks the situation "could have been handled better."

And while Wall Street continues its spending spree as banks scramble to attract junior talent, the frenzy has some raises getting rolled out in a confusing and choppy manner.

Read the full story at the link in our bio.

Story by Samantha Stokes.

(Credit: Samantha Lee/Insider)

node.text:
Data shows that office investment is down 30% through July compared with the same period in 2019. Some are taking this as a sign that office demand will permanently drop thanks to an era of remote work. 

Investors who buy and sell office space are closely tracking the office market for signs of a return to normal or their worst-case scenario: a long-term decline in the need for physical workplaces.

This data gives a breakdown of the cities which have been impacted the most by the lack of need for a physical office.

To read more and see which other cities feature on the list, click the link in our bio.

Story by Alex Nicoll.
